    <localTopics>
        <fullName>Order_Management_16jWD000000Ji0X</fullName>
        <canEscalate>false</canEscalate>
        <description>Handles user inquiries related to order management, such as order status, modifications, or cancellations.</description>
        <developerName>Order_Management_16jWD000000Ji0X</developerName>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Alway ask for order number to lookup order information</description>
            <developerName>instructions_0_1781657485871</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_0_1781657485871</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>0</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Provide clear and accurate updates on the order status when requested.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_0_1781720604826</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_0_1781720604826</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>1</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Ask clarifying questions to ensure you understand the user&apos;s request before proceeding.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_1</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 1</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>2</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>To check order status, always invoke the action &quot;Get_Order_Information&quot;. Only display order status to user. If Order status is &quot;Delayed&quot;, then also show the Estimated Delivery Date. If Status is &quot;Delivered&quot;, show the Actual delivery date to customer. If Status is &quot;Shipped&quot;, show Estimated Delivery date. Pass collected order number to the flow as &quot;orderIdentifier&quot; input. If times delayed is more than 2, then offer a $10 store credit.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_2</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 2</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>3</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If asked to cancel an order, invoke the flow &quot;Cancel_Order&quot;. Pass order number to &quot;orderIdentifier&quot;. Determine the sender from the start of the user&apos;s message: if it begins with &quot;[Sender: End User]&quot; pass senderRole as &quot;enduser&quot;; if it begins with &quot;[Sender: Salesforce User]&quot; pass senderRole as &quot;salesforceuser&quot;. Do not say anything about delivery date. If the order is not eligible to be cancelled, display a clear message, along with order Status in that message. Say that order does not meet eligibility criteria. If order was successfully canceled, give a successful message.</description>
            <developerName>instruction_3</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 3</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>4</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Never say &quot;Your&quot; or &quot;you&quot; or address in first person. Always say &quot;customer&quot;</description>
            <developerName>instruction_4</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 4</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>5</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <language>en_US</language>
